{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-23T03:47:16.355Z","tool_name":"replace","tool_id":"replace_1779508036355_1","parameters":{"new_string":"import math\nimport os\nfrom collections.abc import Mapping\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\n\n# PRD §7.5.2 / CC-083: the entire fatigue feature is gated by\n# ``CYPHERCLAW_V2_FATIGUE``, default OFF.\nCYPHERCLAW_V2_FATIGUE_ENV = \"CYPHERCLAW_V2_FATIGUE\"\n_FATIGUE_TRUE_VALUES = frozenset({\"1\", \"true\", \"yes\", \"on\", \"enabled\"})\n\n\ndef fatigue_enabled(env: Mapping[str, str] | None = None) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Return True iff ``CYPHERCLAW_V2_FATIGUE`` is set to a truthy value.\n\n    Default OFF: an unset, empty, or non-truthy value resolves to False.\n    \"\"\"\n    source = os.environ if env is None else env\n    raw = source.get(CYPHERCLAW_V2_FATIGUE_ENV)\n    if raw is None:\n        return False\n    return raw.strip().lower() in _FATIGUE_TRUE_VALUES\n\n\n# PRD §7.5.2 / CC-080: half-life of ~30 seconds for the exponential decay.\n","old_string":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\n\n# PRD §7.5.2 / CC-080: half-life of ~30 seconds for the exponential decay.\n","instruction":"Implement the CYPHERCLAW_V2_FATIGUE environment flag and an enabled check, consistent with the pattern in affective_state_bus.py.","file_path":"my-claw/tools/expression/fatigue.py"}}
{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-05-23T03:47:16.376Z","tool_id":"update_topic_1779508036111_0","status":"success","output":"## 📂 Topic: **Lead: Tasks T-009, T-010, T-011 - Fatigue Hardening**\n\n**Summary:**\nI am moving to implement the remaining fatigue-related tasks in Sprint 0. This involves adding the `CYPHERCLAW_V2_FATIGUE` environment flag to gate the feature, ensuring the counter correctly handles long recovery silences, and adding comprehensive unit tests to verify decay, threshold gating, and recovery behavior. This will complete the fatigue system's core implementation.\n\n> [!STRATEGY]\n> **Intent:** Implementing Tasks T-009, T-010, and T-011: Fatigue recovery, env-gate, and comprehensive testing."}
